      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 214: resetConnectionBackoff() clears the failure map but leaves any already armed retry timer active. After a connectivity change or restart, an old timer can still fire later and call maintainBuckets(), causing unexpected extra maintenance/connection attempts even though the backoff state was explicitly reset. Cancel the timer and clear retryArmed_/retryAt_ when resetting backoff.\n```suggestion\nvoid\nSwarmManager::resetConnectionBackoff()\n{\n    std::lock_guard lock(mutex);\n    connectionFailures_.clear();\n    if (retryTimer_)\n        retryTimer_-\u003ecancel();\n    retryArmed_ \u003d false;\n    retryAt_ \u003d {};\n}\n```",
