      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 223: The exponential delay calculation can overflow before the clamp if backoffBase_ is large in tests or future configuration, because the duration multiplication is performed before comparing to backoffMax_. Compute the multiplier from the max/base ratio or clamp before multiplying to avoid undefined/implementation-dependent overflow behavior.\n```suggestion\n    auto exponent \u003d std::min(failure.consecutiveFailures - 1u, 31u);\n    auto delay \u003d backoffBase_;\n    while (exponent-- \u003e 0 \u0026\u0026 delay \u003c backoffMax_ / 2)\n        delay *\u003d 2;\n    if (delay \u003e backoffMax_)\n        delay \u003d backoffMax_;\n```",
