      "side": 1,
      "message": "Partially addressed in patch set 2, deliberately without changing the dhtnet callback signature in this patch: SwarmManager::restart() now also clears all backoff state (in addition to connectivityChanged()), so failures caused by local conditions before a shutdown/re-bootstrap never delay the new bootstrap. Remaining exposure is bounded: a local-origin failure can delay retries of an otherwise reachable node by at most one backoff window until the next connectivity event or incoming channel from that node (which clears its entry), and the first attempt of any node is never gated. Plumbing an explicit failure reason through ConnectionManager::connectDevice() and its callbacks is a larger dhtnet API change, noted as follow-up work.",
